# Thordata MCP Server - Cursor IDE Rules

## Code Style
- Use Python 3.10+ type hints
- Follow PEP 8 style guide
- Use async/await for all I/O operations
- All code and comments must be in English (no Chinese characters)

## Architecture
- Tools are organized in structured namespaces: `serp.*`, `universal.*`, `browser.*`, `tasks.*`, `proxy.*`
- High-level entrypoints: `search`, `scrape`, `task_run` (for LLM convenience)
- All tools must use `@handle_mcp_errors` decorator
- All responses must use `ok_response()` or `error_response()` from utils

## Error Handling
- Use centralized error handling via `handle_mcp_errors` decorator
- Return structured error responses with codes (E1001, E2001, etc.)
- Never raise exceptions directly from tool functions

## Testing
- Test all four major scraping categories: SERP, Web Unlocker, Browser, Web Scraper Tasks
- Ensure 100% coverage of 120+ Web Scraper Tasks via `tasks.*` tools
- Verify batch operations work correctly (SERP batch, Universal batch)
